      </arrangement>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_4215cfe0b1e39bb1cc24fceb2e5ad9a6">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The materials in the collection relate to Currier's career as a pianist and faculty member at the Yale School of Music. Included are letters, programs, reviews, lecture notes, posters, and a few photographs. Currier included a number of sound recordings with his Papers. These include solo performances by Currier, and collaborations with other Yale School of Music faculty members. To access these recordings, please contact the Historical Sound Recordings department.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <relatedmaterial id="aspace_1f88561eed25ac7bfcd25e71912391c6">
         <head>Related Materials</head>
         <p>Researchers may also wish to consult the Yale School of Music Papers (MSS 3), also held by the Irving S. Gilmore Music Library.</p>  
      </relatedmaterial>
